WHAT IS IT?
-----------

  'TurnAbout' is a Workbench game that is played on a 7 by 7
spaces board which is filled with tiles that occupy 2 spaces.
The idea is to 'pivot' these tiles so the empty space is moved
on every position, and ends at the lower right position of the
game board.

  A tile can be pivoted if it is located next to the empty space,
so the tile can pivot there. The empty space will then move to
the former position where that portion of the tile was occupying
before it pivoted, and the former position of the empty space
will be marked by a coloured octagonal shape. Note that any tile
can pivot from one side of the game board to the other, if, of
course, the empty space is at the other side...

  Complete the game in the least amount of moves.

  Have fun!

